                <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X,d)]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/ca-000K/" title="Metric Space" uri="http://localhost:8000/ca-000K/" display-uri="ca-000K" type="local">Metric Space</fr:link> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(Y,\rho )]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/ca-001F/" title="Complete Metric Space" uri="http://localhost:8000/ca-001F/" display-uri="ca-001F" type="local">Complete Metric Space</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{n}\colon  X\to  Y]]></fr:tex> be a sequence of functions. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(f_{n})]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/ca-002A/" title="Uniform Convergence" uri="http://localhost:8000/ca-002A/" display-uri="ca-002A" type="local">uniformly convergent</fr:link> if and only if it is <fr:link href="/ca-002B/" title="Uniformly Cauchy" uri="http://localhost:8000/ca-002B/" display-uri="ca-002B" type="local">Uniformly Cauchy</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
